Italy’s Berlusconi Says Had ‘Long’ Conversation With Merkel

-- B y   C h i a r a   V a s a r r i
-- 
2011-10-22T19:32:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-22/italy-s-berlusconi-says-had-long-conversation-with-merkel.html
Prime Minister  Silvio Berlusconi 
said he had a “long” conversation with German  Chancellor
Angela Merkel  today.  Asked whether Merkel is convinced by the measures Italy has
taken, Berlusconi said: “I think so.” He spoke to reporters
today in Brussels after a meeting of European conservative
leaders.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Chiara Vasarri in Milan at 
